Diagnosis.
Male: without paired glands on pronotal disc (
Fig. 11
), pronotal depression broad and deep (
Fig. 26
), humeral setal patch present (
Fig. 3
), scutellum pale (
Fig. 3
), tergite 8 medially lobed (
Fig. 85
), penis smooth sided with acutely attenuated apex (
Fig. 98
) and minute median tooth in lateral view (
Fig. 125
). Female: frontoclypeus medially keeled (as male, 
Fig. 11
), antennomeres 1–3 pale and 4–11 dark brown to black (
Fig. 19
), scutellum pale, ventrite 5 yellow except laterobasal dark patches (
Fig. 47
), pygidium wholly brownish-yellow with rounded apex (
Fig. 47
), apical margin of ventrite 5 shallowly concave (
Fig. 47
).
